values:
Since it has closed down without much warning, I have struggled to gather all the fics I posted there and not here. 

I used to post my long or WIP fics there cos it all stayed under one link, unlike here, and then once complete, here. 

So, I am going to spend the next few hours uploading my fics here that I only posted there, unless I find another site like the resource. And no, I am not using fanfiction.net cos for me it is a bit of a bitch.

Abbyforever

Which NCIS Character Are You?

Congratulations! You are most like lab technician and evidence analyst Abigail "Abby" Sciuto! You are always cheerful and effervescent. Some people would say you are a little eccentric and strange, but that's what makes you so great! You are intelligent and sarcastic, making everyone's day. The world needs more cheerful people like you!

TITLE: ALL THAT I AM Pairing: Tabby Warning: None really. Tabby fluffiness. Spoilers: None that you will notice unless you have seen the ep. Therefore I am not spoiling anything. Name of the ex is stolen from the show. Rating: 15. Nothing really to be worried about. Not even any swearing, if my memory serves me. Author's note: Again jumping in time. Backwards. Oh, and cos I am such a visual writer, I went off and found Abby's dress. Only it is all red when my version is red, black and white. Doesn't matter. You guys are imginative. Abby's dress: http://i73.photobucket.com/albums/i238/Abbyforever2/4523212.jpg ALL THAT I AM See you prime for giving in I give you all that I am "Abby, Gibbs wanted me to check on those results." Tony said as he entered the lab. "Gibbs just left. He's gotta give me at least ten minutes." Abby complained. "Okay, so maybe I'm lying." Tony admitted wrapping his arms around Abby. "Gibbs didn't send me down here." "What's going on here?" She asked. "About dinner tonight..." He started. "I wanted it to be a perfect romantic evening but now we have a case." "Aw, that's sweet. And of course a case came in. Just our luck." She said putting her arms around his neck. "So, since we'll be stuck here all night, I thought we could have lunch together now." Tony suggested hopefully adding a classic smile for emphasis. "Okay. Did Gibbs approve?" She asked. "Yeah. So long as we bring back coffee." Tony said and they laughed. "Of course." "What was the big deal about dinner tonight?" Abby asked as they sat at the cafe for lunch. "Well, as you may or may not remember, this is exactly one year since we got together." He said. "You remembered the date? I thought guys didn't do anniversaries until they got married. And even then." Abby said. "How could I forget? And to celebrate this day, I got you a little something." He said pulling out a little bag. Abby's eyes widened. "Oh, I didn't get you anything. I feel so bad now. I thought you wouldn't care about today." She said feeling incredibly guilty. "I don't want anything other than for you to like your gift." "Okay." She said opening the bag to find a small jewelry box. "You didn't?" She asked pulling the box out. By the time she looked back up, he was on one knee in front of her with a single black rose in his hand. "I did." He admitted. "You little sneak. I had no idea." Abby said taking the beautiful ring out of the box. The black diamond sparkling with the light. "Well, will you marry me?" He asked after what felt like forever. "Of course." She said grabbing him up by his collar and kissing him. And I breathe where you breathe Let me stand where you stand With all that I am "So, what about this one?" Tony asked running his hand across her bare back, as they lay in bed. "The cross? Isn't that obvious?" She asked. "Probably, yeah. And this?" He asked kissing her wrist. "That one? My favorite shape is the triangle, and three being my favorite number, I thought of that. And it kinda represents life, up, then down, then up again." She explained. "Very profound. You like the number three?" "Oh yeah. That's why I have always loved the name Trinity." Abby revealed. "That's a name?" Tony asked. "Now it is?" Abby said definitely with the look on her face that he had to laugh. "I think it's gorgeous. Any other kids names you have planned?" He asked slightly teasing "I don't have kid's names in my mind. Not even Trinity. It's just a name I love." "You don't? I know you're not like other women but I still thought you all did that." "I never pictured myself with a child." Abby said turning over pulling the sheet with her. Tony was leaning in his elbows so he could look at her properly. "Why not?" Tony asked. "Me, a mother? I can't see it." "I definitely can." He said leaning down to kiss her. I would give my life to save you I stand guarding at your door I give you all that I am "Abby, get down!" Tony yelled and Abby immediately listened. "What the hell?" She asked when Tony stopped firing. "What's going on in here?" Gibbs asked as he bolted in from the elevator. He had heard the yelling and the gun-shots. Also another sound that he now knew was glass shattering. There was an unidentified man lying in the glass under the now broken window. "I came in here and saw a man watching Abby through the window. When he saw me, he pulled a gun, so I shot the window out. He fell through it. I don't even know if he was hit by the bullet." Tony explained holding Abby tightly, and protectively. "Are you okay, Abs?" Gibbs asked. "Fine, now." She said burying herself deeper into Tony's arms. Gibbs approached the man lying on the ground. He was breathing and had a strong pulse. The bullet had hit his shoulder and his debilitation was from the fall through the window. "Do you know this guy, Abby?" Gibbs asked turning him around. "Um..." She said getting up and walking away from Tony. "That's my ex Billy-Bob." "The one that tried to run you over with a motorbike? The one with intimacy issues?" Tony asked. "That's the one. He got a little stalker-ish after I broke up with him." Abby revealed. See your faith in me subsiding See you prime for giving in I give you all that I am "Kate, I can't do this?" Abby called out. "Come out and I'll help you with it." She called back not worried. "I'm not talking about the dress." Abby said walking out in the beautiful gown that looked inspired by Emily the Strange. "What are you having trouble with." Kate asked finishing her make-up. "This." Abby said sadly. "What?" "Getting married. What am I thinking?" Abby asked. "What's the matter, honey?" Kate asked sitting next to Abby trying not to crease her dress. "I don't know. I'm not ready for this." "You love him, don't you?" "Of course." "So what are you afraid of?" She asked. "I don't know. I just suddenly can't breathe." Abby said. "It's the dress." Kate teased. "Aside from that." Abby added laughing too. "That too, though. This dress is gonna cause waves." "You think people think they'll get any different?" "You really such a comedian today." Abby said lightly punching her maid-of-honor's arm. "Thank you." "It's not that I care what people think. But maybe I am just taking this whole wedding thing too lightly." "You're not, I can tell you that. And the dress isn't to be disrespectful, it's you. And Tony is gonna love it." Kate assured her. "You think?" Abby said looking down at the dress. "That's cos I have cleavage in it." She added. "Now who's the comedian? Even though I'm sure that wont go unappreciated by Tony. It is a stunning dress." "Thank you. You reckon I'm cut out of this whole marriage thing?" Abby asked and the serious look in her eyes caught Kate. "More than you know. Plus, there is no way you are ever going to be a traditional wife. No way." "That's true." "You look so stunning tonight. Have I mentioned that yet?" Tony asked dipping Abby and then bringing her back up. "Only a million times. Not that I mind." Abby said leaning her head on his shoulder. Her dark hair in curls pinned high on her head with a red ribbon running across it to line her fringe which was pinned to the side, swooping slightly over her forehead. "Then I'll have to say it again." He said kissing her blood-red lips. Lay your head upon my shoulder Lay your hand within my hand I give you all that I am Abbyforever
